<text id="A7159T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Scott writes about difficulties in acquiring rent money for the month and requests assistance, asking if the AMA can "apply again to Gov't for aid this month."</p> 
</div1> 
<div1 type="figure" id="d4">
<p>American Missionary Association letterhead</p> 
</div1> 
<div1 type="envelope" id="d5">
<p></p> 
</div1> 
</front> 

<body id="d6">
<div1 type="letter" id="d7">
<head>
<name type="recipient">W E Whiting Esq</name> 
<name type="place">Mission Home Staunton Va</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1869-05-01">May 1<hi rend="super">st</hi> 1869</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear Sir</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>You will perceive by reference to my <hi rend="underline">Acct</hi> (you perceive) that by the timely aid of the Government I have been able to pay the rent on the school house for the month of April.  The rent for the present month (May) is demanded in advance, and all my attemts to raise it seem fruitless.  We have 10 days of grace yet left and if it is not obtained by that time we shall have to see the school turned out of the building, or I shall have to advance the money from my own pocket.</p>
	<p>Can not you apply again to the Gov't for aid this month, as you or Mr Smith were successful in April</p>


<closer>
<salute>Very Respectfully</salute> 
<signed>John Scott</signed> 

<name type="place">N. Y.</name> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
